Vent Stage

At the end of the Plasma Stage, the RF energy is turned off and the process chamber is vented to the atmosphere through a bacteriological (HEPA) filter. The chamber is pumped down again to 1 Torr and then again vented to the atmosphere.

At the end of the second vent stage, which is the end of the sterilization cycle, an audible alarm tells the operator that the door may be opened and the sterilized contents removed from the process chamber. The printer prints a summary of cycle parameters, and the LCD displays “Process Complete.”

