# Página 163

**Equipo:** Sistema de esterilización STERRAD 100

Uncrating the System

The Accessory Installation Kit consists of two boxes.  One is on top of the unit, the other is inside the cassette chute.  The side of the crate that forms the ramp is marked at the bottom of the crate.  Be sure the ramp and ramp supports are securely positioned before moving the system.

1.  Position the crate on a level surface so that the ramp side faces an open area large enough for the ramp to be extended and the unit removed..

2.  Cut the banding and immediately dispose of it.

3.  Using a screwdriver remove the two clips holding the ramp in place.

    Note:  The crate panels fit together with a tongue and groove mechanism.  The top must be lifted off the sides and the sides must be lifted up from the pallet base.

