RF Test Set-Up and Test

RF Test Set-Up

WARNING:- RF power is present during this operation. do not touch the RF generator or any of the wiring.

! If peroxide has been injected, run the RF for 15 minutes.  Monitor the reflected power display in mV.  The value begins as high as 500 mV then is decreases to a value typically below 100 mV.  If the value begins to climb above 300 mV, there is a potential mismatch in impedance.

! After 500 mTorr is reached and is stable, press a  LONG CANCEL  for the RF Test menu.

! Set-up a Bird Watt meter on the X10 scale.  Reading is on the Kilowatt scale.

! Connect the RF generator to the INPUT of the directional coupler on the Watt.

! Connect the RF interconnect cable to the OUTPUT of the directional coupler Watt.  The RF element arrow should point towards the RF match.

